        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1561438121" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15263713221176738422">After reading Rage of Angles, I am certain that I so much adore the girls who are independent, who love their freedom, who are not driven by what others tell them to do, who are on their own in this Jungle. <br/><br/>I want to know what was not there in this book: love, hatred, agony, betrayal, intrigue, passion, just name it.<br/><br/>Jennifer Parker, Adam Warner and Michael Moretti, I&apos;m in love with these names.<br/>I&apos;m going to be terrified for the rest of my life with the last lines of this book --&gt; <br/><br/>&quot;But she was loo</span>
  <span id="freeText15263713221176738422" style="display:none">After reading Rage of Angles, I am certain that I so much adore the girls who are independent, who love their freedom, who are not driven by what others tell them to do, who are on their own in this Jungle. <br /><br />I want to know what was not there in this book: love, hatred, agony, betrayal, intrigue, passion, just name it.<br /><br />Jennifer Parker, Adam Warner and Michael Moretti, I'm in love with these names.<br />I'm going to be terrified for the rest of my life with the last lines of this book --&gt; <br /><br />"But she was looking into the past, trying to understand when it was that all the laughter died."<br /><br />This is exactly what I felt after finishing it.<br />Just when I used to think that isn't everything going wonderful, that's a bit odd! The author consoled me that that won't be any longer and I went with his ride again.<br /><br />Thanks Ramya for this book. I can't wait to read more of his works :)</span>
