<div id="review_1482688211" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1482688211" />
    <a title="Hayat" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6116230-hayat"><img alt="Hayat" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1420050859p2/6116230.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1482688211?book_show_action=true">Dec 27, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hayat" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hayat" href="/user/show/6116230-hayat">Hayat</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Hayat by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/10517119-pang">Pang</a>
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6116230-hayat?shelf=heroine-independent-spirited">heroine-independent-spirited</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6116230-hayat?shelf=antihero">antihero</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6116230-hayat?shelf=mystery-thriller">mystery-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6116230-hayat?shelf=mishap-madness">mishap-madness</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6116230-hayat?shelf=court-intrigue-politics">court-intrigue-politics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6116230-hayat?shelf=big-books">big-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1482688211" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18442722652226475735"><b>This is my first Sidney Sheldon book and I love it</b><br/><br/>{Thank you Pang for recommending this book to me!}<br/><br/>I stayed awake all night to finish this amazing fast paced, multi-POV thriller with well developed plot full of interesting twists, great character development, brilliant cases with fascinating back stories. More importantly, I couldn&apos;t help admiring the main character, Jennifer Parker, a successful lawyer for sticking up for herself, for being such a fighter, a go-getter, a woman with talent, cou</span>
  <span id="freeText18442722652226475735" style="display:none"><b>This is my first Sidney Sheldon book and I love it</b><br /><br />{Thank you Pang for recommending this book to me!}<br /><br />I stayed awake all night to finish this amazing fast paced, multi-POV thriller with well developed plot full of interesting twists, great character development, brilliant cases with fascinating back stories. More importantly, I couldn't help admiring the main character, Jennifer Parker, a successful lawyer for sticking up for herself, for being such a fighter, a go-getter, a woman with talent, courage and intelligence who is not afraid to show it. At times, Jennifer was weak, she made stupid decisions that destroyed her hard work and reputation but then continued to follow up with more bad decisions concerning men, but that just makes her a deeply flawed interesting character and I like that. The ending was fitting and left space for possibilities. <br /><br />I really admire Sidney Sheldon for letting his main character go crazy, for not being afraid to let his heroine soar high, to be triumphant and suddenly fall to pieces in a major way that had me horrified. Usually, I don't like character devolution, but <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/43328.Rage_of_Angels" title="Rage of Angels by Sidney Sheldon" rel="nofollow noopener">Rage of Angels</a> was well done. I can't wait to try another Sidney Sheldon book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18442722652226475735" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


