<span id="freeTextContainer15822409459621075919">“Being poor is only romantic in books.” <br/>― Sidney Sheldon, Rage of Angels<br/><br/><br/><br/>One of his best.<br/><br/>SPOILERS:<br/><br/>I loved this deeply layered story about Attorney Jennifer Parker, her life in NYC and the two men she loved. This was great from start to finish and remains one of my favorite Sheldon novels.<br/><br/>Seldom have I read a bleaker last paragraph in a book where the main character survives. I was haunted by it. Sheldon was one of the best. In a recent work of fiction I read one of the character sin the book diss</span>
  <span id="freeText15822409459621075919" style="display:none">“Being poor is only romantic in books.” <br />― Sidney Sheldon, Rage of Angels<br /><br /><br /><br />One of his best.<br /><br />SPOILERS:<br /><br />I loved this deeply layered story about Attorney Jennifer Parker, her life in NYC and the two men she loved. This was great from start to finish and remains one of my favorite Sheldon novels.<br /><br />Seldom have I read a bleaker last paragraph in a book where the main character survives. I was haunted by it. Sheldon was one of the best. In a recent work of fiction I read one of the character sin the book disses him as not writing "real books". What the heck does that even mean? It offended me. I am here to say Sheldon's books are as real as you get. I was so moved by Jennifer's story, her love for her son. This was was a terrific book.<br /><br />I hated what happened to Joshua and it was a tough section of the book. I could not stand Adam Warner. Michael? He was hard to hate no matter what awful things he did, although at the end, I stared to.<br /><br />But Adam's wimpyness really kept me from relating to his character. He wanted power so much he was willing to ruin his life and the lives of everyone else. So even though he is a good guy in the book, I could not stand him.<br /><br />4.5 stars. I am still haunted by that last scene. I wonder where Jenifer is now..</span>
