<span id="freeTextContainer7704464223699755297">brief synopsis:<br/>the fall and rise of attorney jennifer parker, and further stuff.<br/><br/>setting:<br/>new york<br/>monaco, france<br/>charlotte, north carolina<br/>las vegas, nevada<br/>acapulco, mexico<br/>singapore<br/><br/>named personalities:<br/>suetonius - a roman historian<br/>michael &apos;mike&apos; moretti - son-in-law of antonio granelli<br/>robert &apos;bobby&apos; di silva - district attorney for the county of new york<br/>antonio &apos;tony&apos; granelli - head of the largest of the five eastern mafia families<br/>camillo &apos;the twitcher&apos; stella - one of michael&apos;s soldati<br/>martin van bu</span>
  <span id="freeText7704464223699755297" style="display:none">brief synopsis:<br />the fall and rise of attorney jennifer parker, and further stuff.<br /><br />setting:<br />new york<br />monaco, france<br />charlotte, north carolina<br />las vegas, nevada<br />acapulco, mexico<br />singapore<br /><br />named personalities:<br />suetonius - a roman historian<br />michael 'mike' moretti - son-in-law of antonio granelli<br />robert 'bobby' di silva - district attorney for the county of new york<br />antonio 'tony' granelli - head of the largest of the five eastern mafia families<br />camillo 'the twitcher' stella - one of michael's soldati<br />martin van buren - a new york governor who went on to be us president<br />grover cleveland - same<br />teddy roosevelt - same<br />franklin roosevelt - same<br />abe 'kid twist' reles - a government witness who had "fallen" out of a sixth-floor window<br />jennifer parker aka wrong-way parker aka yellow canary aka miss potter aka mrs jay - a slender dark-haired girl with pale skin, an intelligent, mobile face, and green, thoughtful eyes<br />j edgar hoover - an fbi director<br />john lindsay - a politician<br />richard nixon - the 37th us president<br />jack dempsey - a professional boxer<br />thomas colfax - the consiglieri for the syndicate<br />lawrence waldman - a judge<br />jimmy serrano - a loanee who got behind and was consequently taught a lesson<br />jesus h christ - a jewish preacher<br />eddie ramos - a murder victim<br />albert 'al' ramos - another murder victim<br />roy riegels - a football player who had carried the ball to his own team's one-yard line<br />abner parker - jennifer's father<br />ammini williams - an indian student<br />josephine collins - a big, rawboned irish girl<br />noah larkin - a young, attractive medical student<br />ben munro - a law student<br />warren oakes - jennifer's criminal law professor<br />kenneth bailey - the ace investigations agency<br />mrs desser - a client of kenneth<br />otto wenzel - the rockefeller collection agency<br />emma lazarus - a sentimental idiot<br />adam 'aw' warner aka mr adams - a member of the disciplinary committee of the new york bar association<br />stewart needham - adam's law partner<br />mary beth - stewart's niece and adam's wife; an ex-secretary of the navy<br />lucinda - adam's bright, black paralegal assistant<br />mrs wenzel - otto's wife<br />mr peabody, jr - a tall, thin lawyer<br />william carlisle - a subject of a summons<br />billy wilder - the screenwriter, director and producer of the apartment<br />clarence connery - a vagrant<br />luna tarner - a hooker<br />francis joseph ryan - a priest<br />abraham wilson - a sing sing convict serving a life sentence<br />raymond thorpe - abraham's fellow prisoner<br />howard patterson - sing sing's assistant warden<br />mr galin - a court clerk<br />ahab - a fictional captain<br />salvatore 'sal', 'little flower' fiore - an almost midget soldati<br />nick vito - a cadaverous-looking soldati<br />joseph 'big joe' colella - a huge soldati<br />carmelina - big joe's strict catholic wife<br />giovanni - michael's father; antonio's distant cousin<br />rosa - michael's wife; only daughter<br />robin hood - a government defying authorithy challenger<br />cynthia ellman - jennifer's secretary<br />lauren bacall - an applause actress<br />andré soltner - lutèce's owner<br />jacqueline kennedy - a fan of lutèce<br />lee browning - a holland and browning partner<br />henri - lutèce's captain<br />connie garrett - a quadruple amputee<br />martha steele - connie's aunt<br />melvin hutcherson - connie's lawyer<br />dan martin - a former football player from northwestern university<br />ted harris - a slight, diffident young man<br />jane eyre - a fictional governess<br />helen cooper - a dowager who was committed at the heathers asylum in westchester<br />loretta marshall - an elementary grade schoolteacher stereotype<br />curtis randall iii aka mr charming - a wealthy socialite<br />melanie - loretta's daughter<br />roger davis - curtis's lawyer<br />mrs franklin - the head of the heathers asylum<br />mrs danvers - a fictional character in rebecca<br />albert - helen's butler<br />dorothy - helen's daughter<br />herbert hawthorne - dorothy's husband<br />archie bunker - a fictional character<br />'three-finger brown' lucchese - antonio's predecessor<br />patrick maguire - a tough, hard-bitten irishman who represented the nationwide motors corporation<br />joey la guardia - a short, compactly built man charged with assault<br />john kennedy - the 35th us president<br />paul richards - a transient accused of robbing a bank<br />fred stevens - a strict disciplinarian judge<br />carter gifford - a federal prosecutor<br />edward munroe - a tall, thin man<br />john trowbridge - the incumbent senator; a veteran politician<br />rick arlen - a rock star<br />grace - a film actress<br />rainier grimaldi - a prince of monaco<br />pele - a great soccer player<br />andré monteux - an elderly doctor<br />edwin newman - a newscaster<br />eric linden - an abortionist in charlotte, north carolina<br />lipschitz - presumably jacques lipschitz<br />noguchi - presumably isamu noguchi<br />miró - presumably joan miró<br />bob clement - jennifer's california client<br />dr spock - presumably benjamin spock<br />ames - presumably louise bates ames<br />gesell - presumably arnold gesell<br />dr harvey - jennifer's obstetrician<br />dr seuss - a children's author<br />joshua adam parker - adam and jennifer's son<br />mrs mackey - a middle-aged scotswoman<br />philip redding - the president of a large oil corporation<br />louis auchincloss - a lawyer<br />george plimpton - a writer<br />peter fenton - jennifer's client who owned a large manufacturing firm<br />marty allen - a comedian<br />abe - a restaurant captain<br />samantha - adam and mary beth's daughter<br />max - a german shepherd puppy<br />clark holman - an attorney with the legal aid society<br />jack scanlon aka frank jackson aka john doe - a kidnaper<br />tammy - a helpless little girl<br />evelyn - jack's wife who died in childbirth<br />earl osborne - the federal prosecutor for the scanlon case<br />barnard - the judge for the scanlon case<br />notaras - a captain connected to the syndicate<br />big joe ziegler - jack's fellow scammer in kansas city<br />mel cohen - another of jack's fellow scammer in kansas city<br />gus stavros - a greek fence<br />mickey nicola - jack's cellmate<br />blanche jackson - jack's sister<br />clara thomachevsky thomas - a the shakers in queens waitress<br />petrone - a syndicate doctor<br />thomas aquinas - a friar who said that when you got to the heart of the evil, there was nothing there<br />vasco gambutti - a syndicate member who killed a cop<br />scott norman - the slain policeman<br />arthur 'fat artie' scotto - a syndicate member<br />eddie 'little eddie' fratelli - a lewisburg inmate on a ten-year sentence<br />al capone - a gangster<br />lucky luciano - a mobster<br />marco lorenzo - a friend of the syndicate convicted of extortion and robbery<br />bebble brothers - presumably george and bert bebble<br />carl stotz - the founder of little league baseball<br />eddie santini - a two-time loser<br />blair roman - head of the second largest advertising agency<br />luis - a mexican lawyer<br />pete - big joe's cousin<br />tommy angelo - a wheel man on a fur heist<br />terry waters - a little league pitcher<br />raul mendoza - a mexican doctor<br />chuck morrison - adam's chief assistant<br />roy wallace - a major general; the quantico base commandant<br />mrs stout - joshua's homeroom teacher<br />miss williams - one of joshua's teachers<br />mrs toboco - another of joshua's teachers<br />craig swan - a major league baseball pitcher<br />morris - a very fat doctor with a red face and nicotine stains on his fingers<br />hieronymus bosch - a dutch painter<br />stefan bjork - an airline steward<br />tony santo - a syndicate member<br />jimmy - a dumb son of a bitch<br />gino gallo - a syndicate member who strangled jimmy<br />charlie corelli - the business manager of the janitor's union<br />wally kawolski - a timid, badly dressed man<br />chou ling - michael's singaporean contact<br />ck tang - a singaporean entrepreneur<br />tan chin tuan - a peranakan banker<br />lee kuan yew - the singaporean prime minister<br />david touh - a reasonable police inspector<br />tan kee seng - an undertaker<br />clin noh - ditto<br />ang yung long - ditto<br />goh soon - ditto<br />jimmy guardino - a syndicate member with the national commission<br />marina - sal's mistress<br />beauty queen - big joe's racing horse<br />tanner - a queens police captain that is on the syndicate's payroll<br />david terry - a justice department agent in charge of creating new identities for witnesses who wished to disappear<br />william bennett - a judge of the supreme court of new york<br />john lester - a former judge<br />hazel - an acquaintance of some stout woman<br />clay reddin - an agent assigned to adam's guard detail<br /><br />typos:<br />p39: it was a prize that took years to attain, and he was not about to deprive someone of it unless he was cerain there was justification.<br /><br />p86: the truth, if he had know it, would have surprised granelli for rosa found her father's business terribly exciting.<br /><br />p328: jennifer shifted in her seat so that she could study inspector spector touh.<br /><br />whew, that was a lot of names.<br />a whole lot.</span>
