<div id="review_800128919" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/800128919" />
    <a title="Riri" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20048793-riri"><img alt="Riri" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459524630p2/20048793.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/800128919?book_show_action=true">Dec 26, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Riri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Riri" href="/user/show/20048793-riri">Riri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer800128919" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14182787832980140684">After weeks and weeks of my friend persuading me to read. Sidney Sheldon books, I finally gave it a try :D It was around 2012 and before that I only read young adult books, and well educational books that I find interesting, he opened me up to the amazing world of books, all genres :p This book is the latest that I have read among all his books. And you have to be patient to wait for an available copy at the library (I can&apos;t afford atm because a lot of expenses at uni, but I promise you, I&apos;m buy</span>
  <span id="freeText14182787832980140684" style="display:none">After weeks and weeks of my friend persuading me to read. Sidney Sheldon books, I finally gave it a try :D It was around 2012 and before that I only read young adult books, and well educational books that I find interesting, he opened me up to the amazing world of books, all genres :p This book is the latest that I have read among all his books. And you have to be patient to wait for an available copy at the library (I can't afford atm because a lot of expenses at uni, but I promise you, I'm buying all his books in the future for my future kids to read and ofcourse future me to read again).<br /><br />Anyway, this book made me cryyyyy a lot. I thought I knew how the story would go but I was wrong. I thought I knew how the ending would go but then again, I was wrong. Great story :D</span>
  <a data-text-id="14182787832980140684" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
